    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix parse_byte() function to handle whitespace separators properly\n\n### Summary\nThe `parse_byte()` function in the nfapi hex parser utility incorrectly handled non-space whitespace characters as separators. When parsing hex values from strings that used tabs, newlines, or other whitespace characters as separators, the function would fail to parse valid hex values and return -1, causing the main parsing loop to terminate prematurely.\n\nThis happened because the original code only checked for space character (' ') as a separator after hex digits, while the updated version uses `isspace()` to properly handle all whitespace characters including tab, newline, carriage return, form feed, and vertical tab.\n\nThe issue manifested when trying to parse strings like \"0xab\\t0xcd\\n0xef\" where tab or newline characters were used as separators between hex values.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/utils/nfapi_hex_parser.c`: Modified the `parse_byte()` function to use `isspace()` instead of explicit space character check for better separator handling, and improved validation order to check character validity before using values.\n"
}